content:
On May 29, the famous girl group BLACKPINK was accused of insulting China, and the topic reached 130 million discussions.
The reason was that in a recent Weibo post celebrating the Macau concert, BLACKPINK used "Macanese" to refer to Macau people instead of "Chinese", which caused dissatisfaction among netizens inside the wall.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
User contribution
On May 29, the famous domestic ACGN website "Moegirlpedia" announced that it would restrict website functions in early June due to "responding to the national call and opening the entire site for semi-protection during the Hangzhou Asian Games."
It is reported that "Moegirlpedia" restricts some functions in early June every year for maintenance, but this is the first time that it has specifically responded to the national call.
It is possible that major domestic websites will open restrictions on website functions for similar reasons in the next few days.
